caption:
@wawa_gatheru here to share some daily rituals and moments of joy with you â˜€ï¸ â¡ï¸

1. A time you felt like your best self: This was the first photo I took of myself after surgery last year. Recovery took a massive toll on my physical and emotional health and this was the first time I felt like myself in a long time. I felt really beautiful here :)

2. A daily ritual: I can be a bit of a hermit at times (understatement) but spending time outside is so important to me. I see it as a practice of grounding myself in my community - human and non-human. 

3. Something feels like home: Finally feeling represented as a Black girl environmentalist. I spent so long feeling alone in the environmental movement and getting to be surrounded by other powerful Black women in this space has been incredible. Itâ€™s been a homecoming for me. 

4. A message from a loved one: I was going through a tough period of time in mid 2020 and asked some close friends for words of support. My friend Brenda sent me this lovely message and I remember ugly crying for a good hour. I look at this message every so often because it reminds me of the abundance of love that I have in my life & how lucky I am to have friendships that see the best in me, even when I donâ€™t myself. 

5. Something that makes you smile ğŸ¥°: Exploring with my friends! My good friend Einass took this picture of me while we were exploring Mexico together after she had handed in her dissertation. Really good times. 

6. One thing you cannot live without (other than Supergoop! ğŸ˜‰): Community. Community is everything. 

We want to see your special moments too! Tag @supergoop for a chance to be featured ğŸ’›
